{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3133027,"name":"Jason","username":"jabl","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/jabl/{size}/183043_2.png","created_at":"2023-01-24T17:58:41.862Z","cooked":"<p>Our drive base is pretty simple, but no matter what, the motors appear to be part of the same MotorControllerGroup - ie they move the same direction, with only the getRightY() joystick input being used.    I’ve  debugged the code down to the feed() method in Controller group and it looks like both left and right motor groups contain valid classes.</p>
<p>We’ve also double checked the SparkMax encoders and the CAN id’s match what we expect.  I’ve included the base code below -  Any thoughts would be appreciated!</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">public class SparkDriveBase extends SubsystemBase 
{

	private CANSparkMax leftMotor1;
	private CANSparkMax leftMotor2;
	private CANSparkMax rightMotor1;
	private CANSparkMax rightMotor2;
        private MotorControllerGroup m_leftMotors;
	private MotorControllerGroup m_rightMotors;   
        private  DifferentialDrive m_drive; 


	/**
	 * Creates a new DriveSubsystem.
	 */
    public SparkDriveBase() 
    {

		leftMotor1 = new CANSparkMax(RobotMap.LeftDriveMotor1, MotorType.kBrushless);
		leftMotor2 = new CANSparkMax(RobotMap.LeftDriveMotor2, MotorType.kBrushless);
		m_leftMotors = new MotorControllerGroup(leftMotor1,leftMotor2);

		rightMotor1=new CANSparkMax(RobotMap.RightDriveMotor1, MotorType.kBrushless);
		rightMotor2=new CANSparkMax(RobotMap.RightDriveMotor2, MotorType.kBrushless);
		m_rightMotors = new MotorControllerGroup(rightMotor1, rightMotor2);

                // invert one side so we don't spin in circles.
		m_leftMotors.setInverted(true);		
		m_drive = new DifferentialDrive(m_leftMotors, m_rightMotors);

	}

	/**
	 * Controls the left and right sides of the drive directly with voltages.
	 *
	 * @param leftVolts  the commanded left output
	 * @param rightVolts the commanded right output
	 */
    public void tankDriveVolts(double leftVolts, double rightVolts) 
    {
		m_drive.tankDrive(leftVolts*driveSensitivity, rightVolts*driveSensitivity);
    }
}
